{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MX4rZ5xaYVv57yUqrGhueV","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dce843f-9ba8-4a40-8e6f-55f9620fecc1","uuid":"44f5bdc7-a60f-4b58-9db5-897f02ac69e5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T09:02:58.169Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.","newString":"- No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:03Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test suite did not verify the `match $X { ... }` wrapper in `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` patterns — AC2 fix could be reverted without test failure. Added guard assertions.\n- **MEDIUM (design gap, not fixed):** `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs. Out of scope per story constraints.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Catch/error-path rules only exclude `error!`/`warn!` levels. By-design per AC wording.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit).","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 5)\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — create-story (2026-03-23T12:14Z)\n\n- **Observation: ACs 1-3 are already implemented.** Code for `getStackLabel('rust')`, `getCoverageTool('rust')`, and the Rust branch in `generateAgentsMdContent()` was added in earlier stories. Only AC4 (`getProjectName` Cargo.toml parsing) is new work.\n- **Risk: Cargo.toml parsing edge cases.** Simple regex parsing without a TOML parser could break on comments, inline tables, or multi-line strings. Known tradeoff per NFR4.\n- **Workaround: sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent.** Had to manually update status to `ready-for-dev`.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — dev-story (2026-03-23T12:18Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 28 docs-scaffold tests pass, 3018/3018 vitest tests pass, 307/307 BATS tests pass. Clean implementation.\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — code-review (2026-03-23T12:25Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml regex only matched double-quoted values.** Single quotes are valid TOML. Fixed to support both.\n- **HIGH: Cargo.toml section regex broke on `[` in values.** Fixed to use `[\\s\\S]*?` with lookahead for next section.\n- **HIGH: Missing showboat proof document.** Created.\n- **MEDIUM: Test assertion too weak** for dependencies-only Cargo.toml. Fixed to verify actual fallback value.\n- **MEDIUM: No test for `[package]` section with no `name` field.** Added.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Mixed quote regex doesn't enforce matching quotes** — acceptable for simple parser per NFR3.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Pre-existing uncovered lines 180, 221-222** in docs-scaffold.ts (unrelated to 8-8).\n\n### 8-8-rust-documentation-scaffolding — verification (2026-03-23T12:30Z)\n\n- All 7 ACs passed. Verifier used a Node.js script (`verify-acs.mjs`) to import and test the functions directly from the dist bundle — creative approach.\n- **OBSERVABILITY GAP on all ACs:** No log events detected for any of the docs-scaffold function calls. These are pure utility functions with no instrumentation — expected for documentation scaffolding.\n- **AC7 indirect:** Test source files not shipped in npm package, so vitest/bats couldn't run in container. Verified indirectly via all 6 functional ACs passing + dev agent's test report.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — create-story (2026-03-23T08:35Z)\n\n- **Risk: Semgrep Rust pattern matching for match arms and closures can be finicky.** AC2 and AC3 depend on this — dev agent should validate rules carefully.\n- **Risk: AC4 tagged integration-required** — verifying `codeharness audit` picks up Rust rules requires a real Rust project with Semgrep installed.\n- **Observation: Pure-config story** — no TypeScript changes, just 3 YAML files. Clean scope.\n- **Observation: computeSummary() rule-name mismatch** — existing analyzer.ts hardcodes JS/TS rule names. New Rust rule IDs won't match, so summary percentages will be off for Rust projects. Outside story scope but a follow-up candidate.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story (2026-03-23T08:43Z)\n\n- **Semgrep validation broken locally:** `semgrep --validate` crashes with `Bigarray.create: negative dimension` on semgrep-core 1.136.0 on macOS. System-wide issue, not rule-specific. Structural validation done via YAML parsing in vitest.\n- **computeSummary won't count Rust rule IDs:** `matchesRule()` in analyzer.ts only recognizes JS/TS rule names. Rust rule IDs won't be counted in summary stats. Architectural limitation — future story needed.\n- **Large rule file:** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` is ~230 lines due to combinatorial explosion. Within NFR1 limit but verbose. Semgrep doesn't support wildcard matching across visibility/async modifiers.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review (2026-03-23T08:48Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** Test fixture missing `tracing::trace!()` namespaced test case. Only bare `trace!()` was tested — a regression in `pattern-not` for namespaced form would go undetected. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit) due to N*M pattern explosion. Could be refactored with `pattern-not-inside` in future.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Error path rules only exclude `error!/warn!` levels, not `info!/debug!`. Matches JS/TS precedent but may cause false positives for devs logging errors at info level.\n- **Coverage gap:** `computeSummary()` won't recognize Rust rule IDs — follow-up story needed.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — verification (2026-03-23T08:54Z)\n\n- **AC2 FAIL:** `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` has invalid Rust pattern syntax. `Err($E) => { ... }` is not a standalone expression — match arms only exist inside `match` blocks. Semgrep parse error: `Stdlib.Parsing.Parse_error`. Zero findings on any input.\n- **Root cause:** Dev agent couldn't run `semgrep --validate` locally (macOS Bigarray crash). Relied on YAML-parsing unit tests which don't validate Semgrep pattern syntax.\n- **Fix needed:** Wrap match arm patterns inside full `match` expressions, e.g. `match $X { Err($E) => { ... } }` or use `pattern-inside` with a `match` block.\n- **AC1, AC3, AC4 PASS.** AC5 partial (tests not shipped in container, CLI functional).\n- Story returned to `in-progress` for AC2 fix.\n\n### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — dev-story fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:00Z)\n\n- **Semgrep not installed locally** — Cannot run `semgrep --validate` to confirm the rule parses correctly at the Semgrep engine level. The fix is structurally correct (match arms must be inside match blocks), but full validation requires semgrep-core.\n- No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":58,"oldLines":3,"newStart":58,"newLines":10,"lines":[" "," - **Semgrep not installed locally** — Cannot run `semgrep --validate` to confirm the rule parses correctly at the Semgrep engine level. The fix is structurally correct (match arms must be inside match blocks), but full validation requires semgrep-core."," - No workarounds, no tech debt added. Single-file YAML fix.","+","+### 8-9-semgrep-rules-rust-observability — code-review fix cycle (2026-03-23T09:03Z)","+","+- **HIGH (fixed):** Test suite did not verify the `match $X { ... }` wrapper in `rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml` patterns — AC2 fix could be reverted without test failure. Added guard assertions.","+- **MEDIUM (design gap, not fixed):** `computeSummary()` in `analyzer.ts` does not recognize Rust rule IDs. Out of scope per story constraints.","+- **LOW (not fixed):** Catch/error-path rules only exclude `error!`/`warn!` levels. By-design per AC wording.","+- **LOW (not fixed):** `rust-function-no-tracing.yaml` at 282 lines (93% of NFR1 limit)."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
