Verifier**: Claude Opus 4.6 (black-box)\n**Container**: codeharness-verify\n**Semgrep**: v1.156.0\n**Codeharness**: v0.23.1\n\n---\n\n## AC5: CLI Functional\n\n```bash\n$ docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version\n0.23.1\n```\n\n**Result**: PASS\n\n---\n\n## AC1: rust-function-no-tracing — Detects Rust Functions Without Tracing\n\n### Validation\n\n```bash\n$ docker exec codeharness-verify semgrep --validate \\\n    --config /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-function-no-tracing.yaml\nConfiguration is valid - found 0 configuration error(s), and 1 rule(s).\n```\n\n### Test File (`/tmp/rust-test/test_ac1.rs`)\n\n```rust\n// POSITIVE: should be detected (no tracing)\nfn no_tracing_function() {\n    let x = 42;\n    println!(\"hello\");\n}\n\npub fn pub_no_tracing() {\n    let y = 10;\n}\n\nasync fn async_no_tracing() {\n    let z = 1;\n}\n\n// NEGATIVE: should NOT be detected (has tracing)\n#[tracing::instrument]\nfn instrumented_function() {\n    let x = 42;\n}\n\n#[instrument]\npub fn instrumented_pub() {\n    let y = 10;\n}\n\nfn has_tracing_call() {\n    tracing::info!(\"doing work\");\n    let x = 42;\n}\n\npub async fn has_debug() {\n    tracing::debug!(\"starting\");\n    let z = 1;\n}\n\nfn has_bare_macro() {\n    info!(\"bare macro\");\n    let x = 1;\n}\n```\n\n### Scan Output\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│ 3 Code Findings │\n└─────────────────┘\n\n    /tmp/rust-test/test_ac1.rs\n     ❱ rust-function-no-tracing\n          Rust function without tracing instrumentation — observability gap\n\n            2┆ fn no_tracing_function() {\n            3┆     let x = 42;\n            4┆     println!(\"hello\");\n            5┆ }\n            ⋮┆----------------------------------------\n            7┆ pub fn pub_no_tracing() {\n            8┆     let y = 10;\n            9┆ }\n            ⋮┆----------------------------------------\n           11┆ async fn async_no_tracing() {\n           12┆     let z = 1;\n           13┆ }\n```\n\n- **3 true positives** detected (fn, pub fn, async fn without tracing)\n- **0 false positives** (5 negative cases all correctly excluded: `#[tracing::instrument]`, `#[instrument]`, `tracing::info!()`, `tracing::debug!()`, bare `info!()`)\n\n**Result**: PASS\n\n---\n\n## AC2: rust-catch-without-tracing — Detects Err Match Arms Without Tracing\n\n### Validation\n\n```bash\n$ docker exec codeharness-verify semgrep --validate \\\n    --config /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-catch-without-tracing.yaml\nConfiguration is valid - found 0 configuration error(s), and 1 rule(s).\n```\n\n### Test File (`/tmp/rust-test/test_ac2.rs`)\n\n```rust\n// POSITIVE: should be detected (Err arm without tracing)\nfn handle_result() {\n    match some_operation() {\n        Err(e) => {\n            println!(\"error: {}\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// NEGATIVE: should NOT be detected (has tracing)\nfn handle_result_traced() {\n    match some_operation() {\n        Err(e) => {\n            tracing::error!(\"failed: {}\", e);\n            println!(\"error: {}\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn handle_result_warn() {\n    match some_operation() {\n        Err(e) => {\n            tracing::warn!(\"warning: {}\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfn handle_result_bare() {\n    match some_operation() {\n        Err(e) => {\n            error!(\"failed: {}\", e);\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Scan Output\n\n```\n┌────────────────┐\n│ 1 Code Finding │\n└────────────────┘\n\n    /tmp/rust-test/test_ac2.rs\n    ❯❱ rust-catch-without-tracing\n          Rust error match arm without tracing — observability gap\n\n            3┆ match some_operation() {\n            4┆     Err(e) => {\n            5┆         println!(\"error: {}\", e);\n            6┆     }\n```\n\n- **1 true positive** detected (Err arm with only `println!`)\n- **0 false positives** (3 negative cases correctly excluded: `tracing::error!`, `tracing::warn!`, bare `error!`)\n\n**Result**: PASS\n\n---\n\n## AC3: rust-error-path-no-tracing — Detects Error-Path Closures Without Tracing\n\n### Validation\n\n```bash\n$ docker exec codeharness-verify semgrep --validate \\\n    --config /usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/patches/observability/rust-error-path-no-tracing.yaml\nConfiguration is valid - found 0 configuration error(s), and 1 rule(s).\n```\n\n### Test File (`/tmp/rust-test/test_ac3.rs`)\n\n```rust\n// POSITIVE: should be detected (error closures without tracing)\nfn map_err_no_trace() {\n    let result = some_op().map_err(|e| {\n        println!(\"error: {}\", e);\n        MyError::from(e)\n    });\n}\n\nfn unwrap_or_else_no_trace() {\n    let val = some_op().unwrap_or_else(|e| {\n        println!(\"fallback: {}\", e);\n        default_value()\n    });\n}\n\n// NEGATIVE: should NOT be detected (has tracing)\nfn map_err_with_trace() {\n    let result = some_op().map_err(|e| {\n        tracing::error!(\"failed: {}\", e);\n        MyError::from(e)\n    });\n}\n\nfn unwrap_or_else_with_trace() {\n    let val = some_op().unwrap_or_else(|e| {\n        tracing::warn!(\"using fallback: {}\", e);\n        default_value()\n    });\n}\n\nfn map_err_bare_macro() {\n    let result = some_op().map_err(|e| {\n        error!(\"failed: {}\", e);\n        MyError::from(e)\n    });\n}\n```\n\n### Scan Output\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│ 2 Code Findings │\n└─────────────────┘\n\n    /tmp/rust-test/test_ac3.rs\n    ❯❱ rust-error-path-no-tracing\n          Rust error-path closure without tracing — observability gap\n\n            3┆ let result = some_op().map_err(|e| {\n            4┆     println!(\"error: {}\", e);\n            5┆     MyError::from(e)\n            6┆ });\n            ⋮┆----------------------------------------\n           10┆ let val = some_op().unwrap_or_else(|e| {\n           11┆     println!(\"fallback: {}\", e);\n           12┆     default_value()\n           13┆ });\n```\n\n- **2 true positives** detected (`map_err` and `unwrap_or_else` without tracing)\